British Petroleum Co Plc's proposedcapitalization share issue, announced earlier today in London,will result in each of the company's ADRs representing 12ordinary shares, up from the current four, a BP North AmericaInc spokesman said.    He explained that the proposed capitalization share issue,which is subject to the approval of shareholders at anextraordinary general meeting to be held April 30, immediatelyfollowing the annual general meeting, is effectively athree-for-one stock split. Reuter&#3;